---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';

const siteName = import.meta.env.LANDING_SITE_NAME?.trim() || 'careersim.local';
const contactEmail = import.meta.env.LANDING_CONTACT_EMAIL ?? 'hello@careersim.local';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Terms of service"
  kicker="Legal · Terms"
  description={`The rules of the road for using ${siteName}: what we provide, what we ask of you, and the limits of an AI practice tool.`}
  lastUpdated="May 17, 2026"
  pagePath="/terms"
>
  <p>
    These Terms of Service (“Terms”) govern your access to and use of {siteName} (the “Service”). By creating an
    account or otherwise using the Service, you agree to these Terms. If you don't agree, please don't use the
    Service.
  </p>

  <div class="legal-callout">
    <strong>TL;DR</strong> · {siteName} is a practice tool, not a guarantee. Use it lawfully, treat AI output as
    a starting point (not advice), and we'll do our best to keep the service running and your data safe.
  </div>

  <h2>1. The service</h2>
  <p>
    {siteName} provides AI-driven simulations of interviews, negotiations, and workplace conversations, plus
    automated coaching feedback. The Service is intended for personal career development. Persona behavior,
    scores, and feedback are generated by AI and may be incomplete, inaccurate, or out of date.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Eligibility and account</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>You must be at least 16 years old to use the Service.</li>
    <li>You're responsible for keeping your credentials confidential and for activity under your account.</li>
    <li>Provide accurate information when signing up and keep it up to date.</li>
    <li>One account per person. Don't impersonate others.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Acceptable use</h2>
  <p>When using {siteName}, you agree not to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Use the Service for anything unlawful, harassing, defamatory, or that infringes others' rights.</li>
    <li>Reverse engineer, decompile, scrape, or attempt to extract underlying models or prompts.</li>
    <li>Use automated means (bots, crawlers) to access the Service except for permitted public pages.</li>
    <li>Resell, sublicense, or commercially redistribute Service output without our written consent.</li>
    <li>Attempt to evade rate limits, security mechanisms, or fair-use restrictions.</li>
    <li>Submit content that is illegal, hateful, sexually explicit involving minors, or designed to harm others.</li>
    <li>Use the Service to make consequential decisions about real people (hiring, firing, scoring candidates).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Your content</h2>
  <p>
    Anything you type, paste, upload, or otherwise submit during a simulation is <strong>your content</strong>. You
    retain ownership of it. By submitting your content, you grant {siteName} a limited, worldwide, royalty-free
    license to host, process, transmit, and display it solely to operate the Service for you — for example, to
    generate persona replies, render transcripts, and produce coaching feedback.
  </p>
  <p>
    Don't submit content that you don't have the right to share — including confidential information from a
    current or past employer that you're under contract to protect.
  </p>

  <h2>5. AI-generated output</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Persona responses, coaching notes, and scores are produced by AI models and may contain errors or
      omissions.</li>
    <li>Output is provided “as is” for practice and self-improvement. It is <strong>not</strong> legal, financial,
      medical, career counseling, or HR advice.</li>
    <li>Don't rely on AI output for real-world decisions without independent verification.</li>
    <li>We may apply automated safety filters to refuse or modify responses that violate our policies.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>6. Our content and intellectual property</h2>
  <p>
    The Service — including site design, code, persona schemas, scenario catalogs, scoring rubrics, and brand
    assets — is owned by {siteName} or its licensors and protected by applicable law. We grant you a personal,
    non-exclusive, non-transferable license to use the Service for its intended purpose during your account's
    lifetime. We reserve all rights not expressly granted here.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Beta and feedback</h2>
  <p>
    Parts of the Service are in beta and may change, break, or be removed without notice. Beta features are
    provided “as is.” If you send us feedback, you grant us permission to use it without obligation.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Fees and billing</h2>
  <p>
    {siteName} is free during the public beta. If we introduce paid plans, we'll announce them clearly and ask
    for explicit consent before charging. Existing free features won't be silently removed.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Termination</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>You may delete your account at any time from the app or by emailing <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>.</li>
    <li>We may suspend or terminate your access if you breach these Terms or to protect the Service or other users.</li>
    <li>Sections that by their nature should survive termination (ownership, disclaimers, liability limits, dispute
      resolution) survive.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>10. Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
  <p>
    THE SERVICE IS PROVIDED “AS IS” AND “AS AVAILABLE,” WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EITHER EXPRESS OR
    IMPLIED, INCLUDING MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, NON-INFRINGEMENT, AND ANY WARRANTIES
    ARISING OUT OF COURSE OF DEALING OR USAGE OF TRADE. WE DON'T WARRANT THAT THE SERVICE WILL BE UNINTERRUPTED,
    ERROR-FREE, OR THAT AI-GENERATED OUTPUT WILL MEET YOUR EXPECTATIONS.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Limitation of liability</h2>
  <p>
    TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, {siteName.toUpperCase()} AND ITS AFFILIATES SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR
    ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, OR ANY LOSS OF PROFITS, REVENUES,
    DATA, OR GOODWILL, ARISING OUT OF OR RELATED TO YOUR USE OF THE SERVICE. OUR TOTAL LIABILITY FOR ANY CLAIM
    RELATED TO THE SERVICE WILL NOT EXCEED THE GREATER OF (A) THE AMOUNT YOU PAID US IN THE 12 MONTHS PRECEDING
    THE CLAIM OR (B) US $100.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Indemnification</h2>
  <p>
    You agree to defend, indemnify, and hold harmless {siteName} from any claim or demand — including reasonable
    attorneys' fees — arising out of your content, your use of the Service, or your violation of these Terms.
  </p>

  <h2>13. Changes to these Terms</h2>
  <p>
    We may update these Terms. If we make a material change, we'll notify you via email or an in-app notice at
    least 14 days before it takes effect. Continued use after the effective date constitutes acceptance.
  </p>

  <h2>14. Governing law and disputes</h2>
  <p>
    These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Delaware, United States, excluding its conflict-of-law
    rules. Disputes will be resolved in the state or federal courts located in Delaware, unless a mandatory
    consumer-protection statute in your jurisdiction grants you the right to sue locally.
  </p>

  <h2>15. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about these Terms? Email <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
